name: Who am I (What's My Code)? #1
description:
‘Who am I (What’s my code)?’ is a series of 3 interactive roadmaps to the world of NFTs. Each of the 3 versions is an edition of 5 and collectors of all 3 versions receive a 1/1 airdrop.

The work breaks down what NFTs are made of in 2021 and what conditions brought them about. Maybe its fully code-based formula can even outlast some of its constituent technologies and help dream them anew.

Behind an encoded poem and it’s 80’s inspired robot face, you can discover digital art for yourself. The modifiable nature of the 11x11 grid allows you to make your own artwork and change it or redo it whenever you want. The work is created responsively for display its shown on, so it’ll always look crisp regardless of scale.

Use this artwork to onboard no-coiners to world of punks & frens.



—————
This artwork is dedicated to the NFT patron Cozomo de’ Medici (a.k.a. Snoop Dogg) & the title is a reference to his debut album’s track ‘Who Am I (What’s My Name)?’

Erwin Laiho is a contemporary artist who deconstructs and explains technology through its materiality.
